<h1>DotGNU Portable Nim</h1>
<p>
Mohan Embar wrote an implementation
of the traditional "Nim" game to demonstrate how to write a
Model-View-Controller application using DotGNU Portable.NET's
System.Windows.Forms implementation.</p>
<p>

<blockquote>
<a href="http://www.getdotgnu.com/contrib/games/dotgnu-nim-20040305.tar.gz">dotgnu-nim-20040305.tar.gz</a>
</blockquote></p>
<p>
After unpacking the distribution, use "<code>ilrun nim</code>" to run
the game.  See the <code>README</code> file in the distribution for further
information.
</p>
<a href="&root;dotgnu-nim-20040305.tar.gz">
<img border="0" width="397" height="345" src="&root;screenshots/11.png"/>
</a>
<p>
Note: The Nim game was originally written for Portable.Net 0.6.0, however
this is an updated version which uses DrawArc (which wasn't implemented
in pnetlib-0.6.0).
</p>
<p>
Please consider helping with implementing more System.Windows.Forms stuff.
</p>
